All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
Appointment
Represents an appointment within the scheduling system, capturing essential details such as title, description, timing, and associated entities like customer, user, and contact.
AppointmentDAO
This class provides data access operations for the Appointment class.
AppointmentForm
Controller for the appointment form screen used to add or modify appointments.
Contact
Represents a contact within the scheduling system, consisting of an identifier, a name, and an email.
ContactDAO
This class provides data access operations for the Contact class.
ConverterUtility
Provides utility methods to fetch and filter specific sets of data from DAOs or from models like Appointments, FirstLevelDivisions, etc.
Country
Represents a country with its unique identifier and name.
CountryDAO
Data Access Object (DAO) class for managing Country entities.
Customer
Represents a customer within the scheduling system.
CustomerDAO
This class provides data access operations for the Customer class.
CustomerForm
Controller class for managing and interacting with the customer form.
CustomersAppointments
Controller class for displaying and managing the customers and appointments scene.
FirstLevelDivision
Represents a first-level division (e.g., state, province) within a country.
FirstLevelDivisionDAO
Data Access Object (DAO) class for managing FirstLevelDivision entities.
JDBC
A utility class for managing JDBC database connections.
LoginScreen
Controller class responsible for handling actions on the LoginScreen.
ReportView
Represents the ReportView controller responsible for displaying various report-based functionalities.
SceneType
Represents a type of scene in the scheduling system's user interface.
SchedulingApplication
Main application entry point for the Scheduling Application.
ScreenUtility
Provides utility methods for managing and changing JavaFX scenes.
TableSearchable
Provides some standard functionality for an objects that is searchable within a table.
TimeUtility
Provides utility methods for time-based operations and checks.
User
Represents a user within the scheduling system, providing an identifier, a username, and a password.
UserDAO
This class provides data access operations for the User model.
